<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>November 16, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Celestial Fists Changed!</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Well, the quest indeed became completable yesterday, and monks across all the servers are now in posession of their epic 'weapon' Celestial Fists.</p><p>The stats  on the item itself has remained the same, but some alterations have been made.</p><p>Now, when you wear them, your fists are changed to 9/16 weapons, and the effect has been changed to a right-click bard-song which now gives 54 ATK, 12 AC and 40% SPELL-based haste.</p><p>Personally I think these are GREAT gloves now, truly worthy of the title 'epic weapon' as it has answered the prayers of so many monks who wanted our H2H skill to be viable again. Thank You Verant for listening to us!</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>November 15, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Patch Day Today.</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Well, the servers are going down any minute (3am PST) for 11 hours!!</p><p>This one is gonna be a Biggie!</p><p>The main change is the upgrade to DirectX7.0. For those of you who have missed the multiple warnings over the last few weeks, if you are not running DX7.0 on your machine, you will not be able to play EQ after the servers come back up.</p><p>Of the other changes taking place, the most exciting for Monks is that our epic quest should be 'fixed'. I estimate about 100 monks across the servers are currently camped out in Trakanons Tooth waiting to complete the quest as soon as the servers come up and the final NPC in the quest is re-activated, but in your haste to complete the quest, please make sure you read my warning <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm7.showMessage?topicID=744.topic">here</a> about the final hand-in. If you do not do it right you will lose everything!</p><p>Well, with the servers down, why not come visit the Monkly Business Chat Room? You can connect either via an IRC client, or via a java applet. Click <a href="/chat/index.php">here</a> for more details.</p>
<p><ul><b>Here is the patch message:</b></p><i><p>***Patch Day***</p><p>Today's patch includes the announced code-updates to use technology included with DirectX 7.  You MUST have DirectX 7 or higher installed in order to play EverQuest.  Please refer to http://everquest.station.sony.com/f_requirements.shtml prior to contacting technical support for procedures prior to contacting technical support.</p><p>Today's patch also includes the new "Sound Engine" that we've been speaking about for some time.  The new sound engine supports additional EAX features and should address the concerns of SBLive users that have been posted in the past.</p><p>*Movelog for Povar and Tarew Marr*</p><p>The /movelog window will be opened for Povar and Tarew Marr on Saturday 11/18 and Sunday 11/19 from 6PM PST (GMT-8)  to Midnight.  All players wishing to have all of their characters moved (on a per-account basis) from those servers to the new split-server should execute "/movelog yes" during the windows.</p><p>The physical character move will take place next week on Tuesday or Wednesday.  Please check the scheduled downtime page of www.everquest.com for a firm time when it is decided.  Remember that corpses will not follow you to the new server, so anyone deciding to move will want to be sure that all corpses are looted prior to the time of the actual move. </p><p>As this patch features new /movelog logic to eliminate problems with people being left behind, players should not count on customer-service intervention after the physical move if they were unable to execute the command during the window.  You will need to be present and execute the command in order to move.</p><p>*Spell Changes*</p><p>-- Pixie Strike: Made it less resistible by reducing the secondary resist.
-- Song of Twilight: Increased duration. Made less resistible by removing the secondary resist. Allowed it to be cast at any time of day.<br>-- Fixed the effect on the Necromancer Epic Quest Item.  The effect was checking resist on each tick instead of running full course.<br>-- Increased the duration of the effect on the Enchanter Epic Quest Item.<br>-- Fixed the "Modulating Rod" so that it can be used by the appropriate races.<br>-- Fixed the Lost Staff of the Scorned<br>-- Maniacal Strength will now correctly overwrite the level 49 strength spell.<br>-- The Death Pact and Divine Intervention spells will now stack appropriately with other spells that have similar effects.</p><p>-- Modified the "Jonathan's" line of songs to remove the "skin" effect in order to allow bards to use them more effectively in combat.  In addition, we made them "Self Only" spells rather than "Single Target" spells in order to allow bards to remain in combat while singing them.</p><p>*General Fixes/Changes*</p><p>-- Fixed a bug that caused an NPC on "Sister's Isle" to attack people who were fighting pirates.<br>-- Removed Paladins as an authorized class for piercing weapons in game since they do not have the piercing skill.<br>-- The "Belt of the River" quest should now work correctly.<br>-- Fixed all known problems with the class-specific epic quests.<br>-- Implemented some new race-specific quests for Iksar.<br>-- Positively modified most Epic Quest Items.  Please check your items to see your changes.  Note:  Not all changes will be evident by looking at the item.<br>-- Fixed the NPC bosses in the Plane of Sky that were not dropping the correct loot.<br>-- Your bread tin will now be returned when baking bread.<br>-- Fixed the Wellford Fargin keyword problem in Firiona Vie.<br>-- Made the "Gravebinder" a magic weapon.</p><p>-- Repaired the Forager Bag.  It was causing people to lose weight when placing items in the bag.  It is supposed to have a weight reduction component, but was not supposed to cause weight loss.</p><p>-- Taunt: Increased effectiveness above level 50.  Previously, creatures above level 50 could not be taunted by means of the taunt skill.  Now, most creatures below the character's level can now be successfully taunted.  As a note, the chance to taunt a creature above 50th level is smaller than that of a creature below 50th.</p><p>*Client Enhancements*</p><p>-- You now have 10 pages of 10 hotboxes each when in full screen mode.<br>-- You can now customize 10 pages of 12 socials each, increasing the total number of available socials by 108.<br>-- Fixed a bug with the keyboard.txt file causing some keys to translate incorrectly.<br>-- Fixed a bug that caused some window positions to save improperly at higher resolutions.<br>-- All key mappings are now stored in the EQCLIENT.INI file.</p><p>-- Fixed all known problems with the clipping plane slider.  Users should now see differences for the entire range of adjustment in zones that support an adjustable clipping plane.</p><p>-- Players on PvP servers will no longer show "[LD]" over their heads when linkdead.  In addition, these same players will no longer show as "LinkDead" in the /who list.</p><p>-- Players can now set custom text colors while in game.  /usercolor:  Usage "/usercolor UserColorNumber R G B" where "UserColorNumber is the number of the color as indicated in the EQCLIENT.INI file, and R, G, and B are red, green and blue respectively.  All changes will be automatically saved to your EQCLIENT.INI file.</p><p>-- OPT files in your EverQuest directory now have a number after the character name indicating the server number.  As such, you will now be able to have characters of the same name on two separate servers with different custom options.</p><p>-- The eqlog.txt file now has a name that includes the server number and character name.  For instance, if your character is named "Bobb", and you are on Server 1, your log text file name would be eqlog_01_Bobb.txt.</p><p>-- Added two new entries to the "Defaults" section of the EQCLIENT.INI file:  AttackOnAssist=TRUE|FALSE - Sets whether or not your autoattack turns on automatically when assisting.  Defaults to "TRUE".  ShowInspectMessage=TRUE|FALSE - Sets whether or not you see the "Soandso is inspecting you" message.  Defaults to "TRUE".</p><p>-- Custom key mappings have been greatly enhanced.  You can now set two keys, a primary and an alternate, for each function in game.  In addition, things that were previously not customizable can now be set to a key of your preference.  Left-click on the key identifier to set the primary key, right-click to set the secondary.</p><p>-- Added the /note command.  /note will append the following text to a file called "notes.txt" in your EverQuest directory.  For instance, typing "/note This is a note" will put "This is a note" on the next line in the notes.txt file.</p><p>- The EverQuest Team</p></ul></i></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>November 3, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Monk Epic Quest Complete on Test Server</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Reports have come in that the epic quest has been completed on Test. Some people doubt the validity of the information, but I have my reasons to believe it as true.</p><p>Here is the big scoop, the final item is NOT a weapon, it's a pair of gloves.</p><p><b><ul>Celestial Fists<br>AC: 15<br>STR +20, STA +10, AGI +10, DEX +10, HPs +100, Sv vs Disease +10, Sv vs Poison +10, Sv vs Magic +10, Sv vs Cold +10, Sv vs Fire +10<br>Effect: Celestial Tranquility<br>Weight 0.1</p></b></ul><p>The good news is that being gloves, the particle effect is on both fists. I dont have a picture as yet, but reports are it's a nice looking effect.</p>The bad news is that it isn't a weapon. Rogues and Warriors both got weapons that increased their damage output by a decent amount. Seeing as most monks 50+ will be max hasted from being grouped with enchanters/bards most of the time anyway, the haste effect is largly meaningless, so all we get is some AC, HPs and Stats, effectively a minimal (from the str) increase in damage output.</p><p>2 notes need to be made:</p><p>1. The quest is still not completable on the live servers, and will not be until the next patch</p><p>2. Before you go totally mad over this, lets wait until the effect is fully tested. Yes I know what the effect does as listed in the spdat.eff file (12ac, 40str, 40% haste) but Verant have played games before, the effect may be completely different, lets wait and see.</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>November 2, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>*GASP* Update!</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>But don't go getting too excited, all I did was 'fix' the broken links to Jekhar's guides in the zone guides section.</p><p>More to come!</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>October 19, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>A week of no updates</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Sorry everyone</p><p>First I was ill, then it was the weekend, and then I had a bad week at work (servers going down, thieves stealing 7 computers, Directors being demanding). The result is that I've been too busy to do an update. I have a load of stuff to put up, and will TRY and find some time to do it tomorrow, but no promises.</p><p>Oh, and yet another Perl programmer has blown out on me, and I am looking for another. If you know Perl, mySQL and Apache, and would be willing to help me by writing a few scripts, please let me know</p><p>Oh, one last thing, the monkly-business email address is being forwarded to another ISP, who seem to have deleted my email account. I will change the redirect when I can find the time, but for now, please email everything to me <a href="mailto:s.blackery@btinternet.com">here</a> instead. Thank you</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>October 12, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>250,000 Hits</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>I'm not very well at the moment, fell ill with Flu last night, and as such will probably not do any updates for a few days (on a related note, please stop sending me the relentless monks guides, I've got 7 copies now).</p><p>However, as at midnight last night, 23 days since the launch, I had registered 250,157 hits, and just wanted to say a big thank you to everyone who has submitted articles and thus helped contribute to what has proven to be a highly successful site.</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#334455"><b><u>October 9, 2000.</u></b></FONT></p>
<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Relentless Monks Zone Guides</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>As some of you may have noticed, Jekhar's 'Relentless Monks' zone guides are now broken links. Seems he stopped playing EQ and took the site down. Someone did send me a copy of those guides a while back, but I threw them away, being content at the time to just link to them.</p><p>If anyone has a copy of those guides, could you please send them to me.</p></FONT></ul>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>Content Updated</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>Caldwyn of Sol Ro sent me a guide to obtaining the sash/headband components, and Congdar Fui sent me an updated version of his guide. Rather than have 2 guides, I have combined them together</p><p>So check out the new sash/headband guide in the Quest Guides section. I think you will agree it is pretty comprehensive now.<p>Also added in the Quest Guides section is Bodi's guide to the Robe of the Whistling Fist.</p><p>Bodi also sent me a link to a guide to the new monk epic quest. This is a work in progress, with all the information up to what we know so far, and with a lot of missing images. I dont want to put incomplete guides up, so I am just going to put a link <a href="http://www.geocities.com/kibadachi_uk/monkepicquest.htm" target ="_blank">here</a> for now, so you can all read up on the current situation and <a href="mailto:bodi.bojangles@cwcom.net?subject=Pictures for the epic quest">email</a> him if you have any of the pictuers he is missing.</p><p>Once it is complete I will add it to the Quest Guides section.</p></FONT></ul>

</td>
